[SEARCH] Resolved result: '[\n  {\n    "Document Name": "ABB_IRB8700_Product_Manual.pdf \\u2014 Page 32",\n    "Full Text": "To manually release the brakes on an ABB IRB 8700 robot, follow these steps, keeping in mind the critical safety warnings:\\n\\n**Safety Precautions:**\\n*   **Danger of Movement:** When holding brakes are released, the robot axes can move very quickly and in unexpected ways. Always ensure no personnel are near or beneath the robot arm.\\n*   **Weight of Arms:** Before releasing the brakes, confirm that the weight of the robot arms will not worsen an injury if someone is trapped.\\n\\n**Procedure:**\\n\\n1.  **Locate the Internal Brake Release Unit:** The IRB 8700 is equipped with an internal brake release unit. This unit has individual push buttons for controlling the brakes of each axis, numbered according to the robot\'s axes.\\n\\n2.  **Power Supply (if not connected to controller):** If the robot is not connected to its controller, you must supply external power to the R1.MP connector on the robot to activate the brake release buttons.\\n    *   The IRB 8700 has two R1.MP connectors: R1.MP-A and R1.MP-B.\\n    *   For axes 1, 2, and 3: Supply 0V to pin 12 on R1.MP-A and 24V to pin 11 on R1.MP-B. Both R1.MP-A and R1.MP-B contacts are used.\\n    *   For axes 4, 5, and 6: Supply 0V to pin 12 on R1.MP-B and 24V to pin 11 on R1.MP-B. Only the R1.MP-B contact is used.\\n    *   **WARNING:** Incorrect connections, such as supplying power to the wrong pin, could result in all brakes being released simultaneously.\\n\\n3.  **Release the Brake:** Press and hold the corresponding button on the internal brake release unit for the specific robot axis whose brake you wish to release.\\n\\n4.  **Re-engage Brake:** The brake will re-engage as soon as you release the button.\\n\\n**Additional Considerations:**\\n*   Always refer to the IRB 8700 Product Manual for detailed diagrams and the exact location of the brake release unit and connectors.\\n*   After any service work that involves removing and refitting the brake release unit, always verify that the push-buttons are not jammed in the depressed position. A jammed button can cause the affected motor brake to be released when power is turned on, leading to serious injury or damage.",\n    "Page Number": "",\n    "URL": "projects/338431745290/locations/global/collections/default_collection/dataStores/linamar-vector-bootcamp/branches/0/documents/abb-irb8700-product-manual-pdf-p32"\n  },\n  {\n    "Document Name": "ABB_IRB8700_Product_Manual.pdf \\u2014 Page 31",\n    "Full Text": "To manually release the brakes on an ABB IRB 8700 robot, follow these steps, keeping in mind the critical safety warnings:\\n\\n**Safety Precautions:**\\n*   **Danger of Movement:** When holding brakes are released, the robot axes can move very quickly and in unexpected ways. Always ensure no personnel are near or beneath the robot arm.\\n*   **Weight of Arms:** Before releasing the brakes, confirm that the weight of the robot arms will not worsen an injury if someone is trapped.\\n\\n**Procedure:**\\n\\n1.  **Locate the Internal Brake Release Unit:** The IRB 8700 is equipped with an internal brake release unit. This unit has individual push buttons for controlling the brakes of each axis, numbered according to the robot\'s axes.\\n\\n2.  **Power Supply (if not connected to controller):** If the robot is not connected to its controller, you must supply external power to the R1.MP connector on the robot to activate the brake release buttons.\\n    *   The IRB 8700 has two R1.MP connectors: R1.MP-A and R1.MP-B.\\n    *   For axes 1, 2, and 3: Supply 0V to pin 12 on R1.MP-A and 24V to pin 11 on R1.MP-B. Both R1.MP-A and R1.MP-B contacts are used.\\n    *   For axes 4, 5, and 6: Supply 0V to pin 12 on R1.MP-B and 24V to pin 11 on R1.MP-B. Only the R1.MP-B contact is used.\\n    *   **WARNING:** Incorrect connections, such as supplying power to the wrong pin, could result in all brakes being 