oting-manual-p296"\n  },\n... <truncated>
Based on the search results, the "programmed force reduced" error (error code 50249) occurs when the force programmed for a robotic tool's tip is greater than the maximum motor torque the system can deliver.

As a protective measure, the robot system automatically lowers the programmed tip force to the maximum motor torque it can achieve to prevent damage to the robot or its tooling.

Recommended actions to address this error include:
*   Reducing the programmed tip force in the robot's program.
*   Checking the force versus torque calibration within the system parameters.
*   Verifying the maximum motor torque settings in the system parameters.

A similar error, "calibration force reduced" (error code 50250), can happen during calibration if the requested force is too high for the tool.

