Error code 40038 is a "Data declaration error".

This error happens when the `LOCAL` attribute is used illegally in a routine variable declaration. The `LOCAL` attribute is only allowed for program data declarations.

To fix this, you can either:
*   Remove the `LOCAL` attribute from the routine variable declaration.
*   Move the variable declaration outside of the routine.

